2026-04-16 07:50:58 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module to Power Supply connection cabling'] hypothesis_explanation="The green LED on the power supply indicates that the power supply is working and is outputting voltage. The red LED on the control module is designed to turn on only if the 12V and 0V lines are swapped between the power supply and the control module (i.e., inverted polarity). This also explains why the lamp doesn't turn on: the diode in the load module blocks current in the case of reversed polarity. The most likely cause is that the cables connecting the power supply to the control module have been connected with the wrong polarity (swapped), causing the inverted cables indicator to light up and preventing current from reaching the lamp."
